cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.DS 

This paper proposes a new decision tree algorithm that can be trained with backpropagation, making it suitable for hierarchical representation learning. This suggests that it belongs to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also evaluates the algorithm on classification and regression tasks, which are common in computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper introduces a new type of decision tree that allows for distributed representations, which could be relevant to the data structures (cs.DS) sub-category.
